%N A391473 a(n) is the smallest positive integer k such that k*R_n has digits with alternating parity, where R_n is the n-th repunit.
%F A391473 a(n) = A110305(A002275(n)).
%F A391473 Conjecture:
%F A391473   a(2*n) = (4060*10^(2*n - 4) + 21)/11, n >= 2.
%F A391473   a(2*n-1) = (208*10^(2*n - 4) + 1)/11, n >= 2.
%e A391473 n |    R_n     |     k    |      k*R_n       |
%e A391473 1 | 1          | 1        | 1                |
%e A391473 2 | 11         | 11       | 121              |
%e A391473 3 | 111        | 19       | 2109             |
%e A391473 4 | 1111       | 371      | 412181           |
%e A391473 5 | 11111      | 1891     | 21010901         |
